The course introduces structuralist, semiotic, comparative, cognitive and other approaches. The course discusses literature as an art and a medium, as part of contemporary mediascapes, among other fictional, scientific, philosophical, and ideological discourses.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course offers an overview of core approaches and methods of literary theory in a wider context of the 20th-21st-century intellectual history and their applications in contemporary research frameworks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students obtain a knowledge of new forms, functions, and the new methods of interpretation and study of literature in the 21st century.
